    "Id": "vehiclechassisdef_IGNIS",
    "Name": "Ignis",
    "Details": "<b>Name: <color=#85DBF6>Ignis Infantry Support Tank</color>\nArmor: <color=#85DBF6>Standard</color>\tTechnology: <color=#85DBF6>Inner Sphere</color>\nMovement: <color=#85DBF6>4/6 (Tracked)</color>\tEngine: <color=#85DBF6>120 ICE</color></b>\n\nThe Ignis was an anti-insurgent vehicle designed for urban assault in the Rim Worlds Republic. Its primary role was to ram buildings, creating breaches for infantry squads to enter. During the Amaris Coup, the Ignis became notorious for its use against civilian targets.\n\nEquipped with four Vehicle Flamers and a single Machine Gun, the Ignis is ideal for combating infantry. Its nine tons of armor, with a focus on frontal protection, make it suitable for ramming structures. A one-ton infantry bay allows for rapid deployment of troops into the breach.",
